  <div class="card" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
    <div class="card-title"><span class="dot"></span>What is metadata and why does it matter?</div>
    <div class="guide-grid">
      <div class="guide-card">
        <span class="g-icon">📧</span>
        <strong>Content metadata</strong>
        <p>Email addresses, usernames, phone numbers, and real names embedded in your message can identify you even after encryption.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="guide-card">
        <span class="g-icon">📍</span>
        <strong>Location metadata</strong>
        <p>Street addresses, city names, GPS coordinates, or landmark references can reveal where you are or where you've been.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="guide-card">
        <span class="g-icon">⏱</span>
        <strong>Timing metadata</strong>
        <p>Even if content is encrypted, <em>when</em> you send a message, to whom, and how often, is visible to network observers. Use anonymising networks like Tor for high-risk communications.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="guide-card">
        <span class="g-icon">📡</span>
        <strong>Channel metadata</strong>
        <p>Your IP address, device fingerprint, and operating system are visible when you connect to any online service. Encryption does not hide these.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px;font-weight:500;">Channel security comparison</div>
      <div class="guide-card" style="background:var(--bg);">
        <div class="channel-row">
          <div class="channel"><span class="c-label">Unencrypted email (Gmail, Yahoo)</span><span style="color:var(--danger);font-size:11px;">⛔ Not safe</span></div>
